{"TopicId":22809,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"[1.12.x] Kerbal Alarm Clock v3.13.0.0 (April 10)","CreatedByName":"TriggerAu","CreatedById":57838,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-04-19T12:01:32Z","PageNum":107,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"kurgut","CreatedById":188918,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-05-12T09:38:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi,\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you know by any chance if it\u0027s possible to entirely disable the stock alarm feature ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s not a big concern at all of course, I was just wondering... \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks ! \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nori","CreatedById":41334,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-05-12T15:27:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224282407\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002222809\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221683884316\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022188918\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kurgut\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, kurgut said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi,\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo you know by any chance if it\u0027s possible to entirely disable the stock alarm feature ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s not a big concern at all of course, I was just wondering... \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks ! \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d love that feature as well. Trigger\u0027s resource panels allows replacing the stock one so I was hopeful the alarm clock could be as well, but alas I haven\u0027t seen a way to do it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"LTQ90","CreatedById":196180,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-12T21:14:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222891039\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002222809\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481980809\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154367\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DomiKamu\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 12/17/2016 at 2:20 PM, DomiKamu said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBug report about \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E v3.8.3.0 \u0026amp; KSP 1.2.2\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cu\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEDITED:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/u\u003E tests/investigations from fresh \u0026amp; unmodded KSP (only \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E) \u002B providing files for support (logs/savegames/screen captures).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi TriggerAu,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFirstly many thanks about \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E, it\u0027s very useful tool and really I love it!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHowever, I have a strange issue when clicking \u003Cstrong\u003EReplace Maneuver Node(s)\u003C/strong\u003E button (when alarm is triggered just before reaching maneuver node),\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t know if I\u0027m alone to have this issue.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#ff0000;\u0022\u003E\u003Cu\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIssue description:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/span\u003E after clicking the button, I can\u0027t remove (nor edit) created node. Also the orange gizmo remains displayed on menus, when I quit game (appears in yellow color, as shown in screen captures).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m using KSP v1.2.2 build 1622, 64-bit version for Windows, non Steam (bought directly from KSP Store couple of years ago).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis issue is easy to reproduce (the best way is to use \u00221-Orbiting Kerbin.sfs\u0022 savegame, however):\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n- Orbit Kerbin, any vessel (I use stock \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EKerbal X\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/em\u003E spaceship).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n- Set a maneuver node anywhere along your orbit (any parameters, it\u0027s not important, for example add just few \u0022prograde\u0022 \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003EdV\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n- From \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E, create an alam related to this maneuver node (kill warp, message, 1 minute).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n- Now warp and wait... when alarm is triggered and warp killed (1 minute before maneuver node - as expected), click once on \u003Cstrong\u003EReplace Maneuver Node(s)\u003C/strong\u003E button, from alarm window.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n- From map view, now try to delete (or edit) created node: nothing occurs. Now quit game to main menu, from menus, the node remains visible (yellow) - as show in enclosed screen captures (PNGs).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#ff0000;\u0022\u003E\u003Cu\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProvided files to help support:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSingle ZIP file (with folder structure) containing logs, whole savegame folder (with ship), and 5 PNGs -\u0026gt; \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/s/82ujwygtaailttn/KSP%20Node%20Bug.zip?dl=0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehere (from Dropbox)\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n-or-\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFolder \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/sh/9xmliqslupkasng/AACwVn_ETV5Tyv5o3zK7uYZ8a?dl=0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehere (from Dropbox)\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOf course, I precise this button isn\u0027t vital for me (really I don\u0027t need this feature yet) and I\u0027ve discovered this issue only by chance.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRegards\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDominique\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(Sorry about some English mistakes, I\u0027m French and I hate online translators).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWith ksp 1.12.5 and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E 3.14 i ve got this same old bug. A maneuver node stay on the vessel. When i leave for the space center it stay displaye and still exist when i leave for the main game menu.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Morbanth","CreatedById":190779,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-12T21:34:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/188918-kurgut/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022188918\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/188918-kurgut/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@kurgut\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/41334-nori/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002241334\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/41334-nori/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Nori\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u00A0I use this one to avoid accidentally creating alarms when manipulating manoeuvre nodes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u002215008\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed5046719544\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/topic/219015-112x-stock-alarm-clock-disabler/?do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:197px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kurgut","CreatedById":188918,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-14T09:44:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224346819\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002222809\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221702416890\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022190779\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Morbanth\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 12/12/2023 at 10:34 PM, Morbanth said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/188918-kurgut/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022188918\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/188918-kurgut/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@kurgut\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/41334-nori/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002241334\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/41334-nori/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Nori\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u00A0I use this one to avoid accidentally creating alarms when manipulating manoeuvre nodes\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah thanks ! I\u0027ve seen this mod and been using it since !\u00A0 \u003Cspan\u003E: )\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GuessingEveryDay","CreatedById":203507,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-02-28T19:33:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey, I\u0027m trying to use Kerbal Alarm Clock 3.14.0.0, but the icon is not showing up anywhere. Toolbar Controller doesn\u0027t have it in the list. I\u0027ve tried reinstalling it, but it\u0027s not working.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m not completely sure what is the issue, as it\u0027s the only mod that\u0027s working.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GuessingEveryDay","CreatedById":203507,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-02-29T22:14:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOkay, it\u0027s just a faulty \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Comprehensive Kerbal Archive Network (a KSP mod manager)\u0022\u003ECKAN\u003C/abbr\u003E installation. Installing it manually works.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RayneCloud","CreatedById":11227,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-05-18T19:33:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes this replace the stock kerbal alarm clock function?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Krazy1","CreatedById":203523,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-05-18T23:03:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224391020\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002222809\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221716060836\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002211227\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RayneCloud\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, RayneCloud said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes this replace the stock kerbal alarm clock function?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell... depends what you mean. Possible answers are:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EThe other way around.\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E came long before the stock clock in KSP 1.12... so the stock clock was supposed to replace \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u00A0 But devs didn\u0027t directly adopt \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E, instead went off and tried to develop something functionally similar. Many people (like me) prefer \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E to the stock clock.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EYes. \u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E and the stock clock are intended to have (basically) the same functionality\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ENo.\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E code does not disable or replace the stock clock. Both run independently in-game.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EYou decide.\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0You can install Stock Alarm Clock Disabler and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E. Then effectively \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E can replace the stock clock.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RayneCloud","CreatedById":11227,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-05-18T23:36:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224391052\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002222809\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221716073405\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022203523\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Krazy1\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n31 minutes ago, Krazy1 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell... depends what you mean. Possible answers are:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EThe other way around.\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E came long before the stock clock in KSP 1.12... so the stock clock was supposed to replace \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u00A0 But devs didn\u0027t directly adopt \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E, instead went off and tried to develop something functionally similar. Many people (like me) prefer \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E to the stock clock.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EYes. \u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E and the stock clock are intended to have (basically) the same functionality\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003ENo.\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E code does not disable or replace the stock clock. Both run independently in-game.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EYou decide.\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0You can install Stock Alarm Clock Disabler and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E. Then effectively \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E can replace the stock clock.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks, I\u0027ll do just that and install both SACD and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Alarm Clock (mod)\u0022\u003EKAC\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}